      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:5:2:138:1",
      "text": [
        " الشُّفْعَةُ لِكُلِّ شَرِيكٍ لَمْ يُقَاسِمْ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Ali Bin hadeed, from Jameel Bin Darraj, from one of our companions, ",
          "from one of the two (5<sup>th</sup> or 6<sup>th</sup> Imam<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The pre-emption is for every partner who has not shared’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "1. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad ibn ‘Isa from Ali ibn Hadid from Jamil ibn Darraj from certain persons of our people who has said the following: “One of the two Imam, (abu Ja’far or abu ‘Abd Allah), ‘Alayhim al-Salam, has said, The right of al- Shuf’ah (pre-emption) of an asset belongs to a business partner who has not yet departed partnership.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
